1331
01:53:22,400 --> 01:53:25,500
It must be here. It must be.

1332
01:53:37,600 --> 01:53:38,800
Don't touch it.

1333
01:53:39,600 --> 01:53:42,000
We have seven minutes.

1334
01:53:47,200 --> 01:53:49,800
Robert, hold this.

1335
01:54:30,600 --> 01:54:32,700
It's cold down here, isn't it?

1336
01:54:32,700 --> 01:54:34,400
What's wrong?

1337
01:54:34,700 --> 01:54:37,300
Cold decreases battery life

1338
01:54:39,200 --> 01:54:41,300
We may have less than five minutes.

1339
01:54:41,700 --> 01:54:43,200
So?

1340
01:54:43,200 --> 01:54:45,900
If I pull the power with less than five minutes...

1341
01:54:45,900 --> 01:54:48,800
...the residual charge won't hold suspension.

1342
01:54:50,300 --> 01:54:53,500
We should leave it here and get clear if we can.

1343
01:54:53,500 --> 01:54:55,800
- At least down here the damage - No!

1344
01:54:55,900 --> 01:54:58,300
- No. Wait! - Father!

1345
01:55:00,400 --> 01:55:02,500
We are live here at St. Peter's Square...

1346
01:55:02,500 --> 01:55:06,200
where, despite a bomb threat, and an order of evacuation...

1347
01:55:06,200 --> 01:55:09,900
...the crowd is actually growing in size As we await an official...

1348
01:55:09,900 --> 01:55:12,000
...announcement from the Vatican spokesman...

1349
01:55:12,000 --> 01:55:14,200
...as to the exact nature of the threat...

1350
01:55:14,200 --> 01:55:18,100
...and whether or not they are treating it as a credible danger.

1351
01:55:25,400 --> 01:55:26,900
This way.

1352
01:55:31,100 --> 01:55:34,400


1353
01:55:59,500 --> 01:56:01,700
A bomb?

1354
01:56:06,100 --> 01:56:10,100
Roberto, this is an emergency. I'll take her up alone.

1355
01:56:14,000 --> 01:56:16,100
He's got clearance.

1356
01:56:41,000 --> 01:56:43,200
Oh, my God.

1357
01:58:44,500 --> 01:58:46,100
Get down!

1358
02:01:38,600 --> 02:01:41,000
Cardinal Strauss?

1359
02:01:41,000 --> 02:01:45,000
It was the Camerlengo. He has saved us all.

1360
02:01:45,100 --> 02:01:49,400
He has saved the Church and he's still alive.

1361
02:01:50,000 --> 02:01:51,900
Praise God. Praise God.

1362
02:01:57,400 --> 02:01:58,900
He is alive.

1363
02:01:58,900 --> 02:02:02,700
He sacrificed himself for all of us.

1364
02:02:30,500 --> 02:02:34,500
You know the worst thing we thought would happen?

1365
02:02:34,600 --> 02:02:38,900
Was that our work would fall into the hands of the energy companies.

1366
02:02:40,900 --> 02:02:43,500
We thought we could change the world.

1367
02:02:43,700 --> 02:02:45,100
So naive.

1368
02:02:45,100 --> 02:02:48,900
No, not naive.

1369
02:02:48,900 --> 02:02:50,900
Innocent, maybe.

1370
02:02:50,900 --> 02:02:53,500
But it's not a crime.

1371
02:02:54,500 --> 02:02:57,000
I'm not so sure.

1372
02:02:58,200 --> 02:03:01,100
Go back to work.

1373
02:03:01,700 --> 02:03:04,100
Change the world.

1374
02:03:22,700 --> 02:03:25,900
A gift, uh, you understand?

1375
02:03:25,900 --> 02:03:28,900
Let's say for Catholics everywhere.

1376
02:03:28,900 --> 02:03:32,600
The Carmerlengo's age shouldn't reach the decision.

1377
02:03:32,700 --> 02:03:35,000
Signori

1378
02:03:35,000 --> 02:03:38,900
you are no doubt aware that the Holy Law of that man is ineligible for election to the papacy.

1379
02:03:38,900 --> 02:03:40,900
He's not a cardinal. He's a priest.

1380
02:03:40,900 --> 02:03:42,800
He's of insufficient age.

1381
02:03:42,800 --> 02:03:46,100
Or maybe there's a way we could consider the possibility.

1382
02:03:46,100 --> 02:03:50,900
I am sorry. The protocols of conclave are not subject to modification.

1383
02:03:50,900 --> 02:03:53,000
I will not call a ballot on this matter.

1384
02:03:53,000 --> 02:03:56,000
But, signore, you would not hold a ballot.

1385
02:03:56,000 --> 02:03:57,400
Surely, you remember?

1386
02:03:57,400 --> 02:04:00,400
You gave up your post as Great Elector.

1387
02:04:00,400 --> 02:04:02,700
They are singing at St. Peter's Square.

1388
02:04:02,700 --> 02:04:05,600
Now, what happened here tonight transcends our laws.

1389
02:04:05,600 --> 02:04:06,800
Has it?

1390
02:04:06,800 --> 02:04:10,100
Is it God's will that we give ourselves over to frenzy?

1391
02:04:10,100 --> 02:04:11,900
Discard the rules of the Church?

1392
02:04:11,900 --> 02:04:14,800
Perhaps we need not discard them.

1393
02:04:15,300 --> 02:04:21,400
Signori, I am thinking now of Romano Pontifici Eligendo numero 60...

1394
02:04:21,400 --> 02:04:23,500
-Acclamation by Adoration. - Exactly, signore. Exactly.

1395
02:04:24,600 --> 02:04:27,800
Yes. If the Holy Spirit speaks through us...

1396
02:04:27,800 --> 02:04:30,400
and we call a man's name out loud...

1397
02:04:30,400 --> 02:04:33,200
That is election by adoration.

1398
02:04:33,200 --> 02:04:35,800
He's God's choice.

1399
02:04:35,800 --> 02:04:40,900
Yes. And the candidate need only be an ordained member of the clergy...

1400
02:04:40,900 --> 02:04:45,900
present in the Sistine Chapel at the moment of his election.

1401
02:04:53,700 --> 02:04:55,500
I think we havn't certain...

1402
02:05:18,900 --> 02:05:20,400
Signor Camerlengo?

1403
02:05:20,700 --> 02:05:21,900
Yes?

1404
02:05:21,900 --> 02:05:25,900
The cardinals ask you to join them in conclave as soon as possible.

1405
02:05:26,100 --> 02:05:27,500
Me?

1406
02:05:27,500 --> 02:05:29,900
Yes, Padre.

1407
02:05:52,200 --> 02:05:53,500
What are you doing?

1408
02:05:53,500 --> 02:05:56,900
Silvano's journals. I want them back.

1409
02:06:21,000 --> 02:06:23,300
Richter said...

1410
02:06:24,200 --> 02:06:26,400
His Holiness suffered from seizures...

1411
02:06:26,400 --> 02:06:29,000
and steps were taken...

1412
02:06:29,800 --> 02:06:31,800
for safety.

1413
02:06:35,900 --> 02:06:39,200
He made sure he was watched he said.

1414
02:06:40,400 --> 02:06:44,400
What if he were trying to give me this key?

1415
02:06:44,700 --> 02:06:47,300
That's the Papal office.

1416
02:06:47,300 --> 02:06:49,300
If the Pope was worried about seizures,

1417
02:06:49,300 --> 02:06:52,600
he must've had Richter install cameras without telling anyone.

1418
02:06:52,600 --> 02:06:55,500
To keep an eye on him for his safety.

1419
02:06:57,100 --> 02:06:59,100
Maybe it records.

1420
02:07:09,800 --> 02:07:11,700
I read the journals, Patrick.

1421
02:07:11,700 --> 02:07:14,500
The scientist kept journals. So?

1422
02:07:14,500 --> 02:07:16,500
You figure prominently in them.

1423
02:07:16,900 --> 02:07:18,100
Really?

1424
02:07:18,100 --> 02:07:22,800
Bentivoglio wasn't just a physicist. He was also a Catholic priest.

1425
02:07:23,100 --> 02:07:27,100
As such, he was deeply conflicted about the implications of his work

1426
02:07:27,300 --> 02:07:29,900
and in need of spiritual guidance.

1427
02:07:29,900 --> 02:07:32,100
Like Galileo.

1428
02:07:32,700 --> 02:07:36,100
About a month ago...he requested an audience with the Pope.

1429
02:07:36,200 --> 02:07:38,000
But you know that.

1430
02:07:38,000 --> 02:07:41,400
You soon granted the audience and you were also present during it.

1431
02:07:41,400 --> 02:07:44,600
The 'God Particle'.

1432
02:07:44,600 --> 02:07:46,600
To actually claim an act of creation. The blasphemy. The arrogance.

1433
02:07:46,600 --> 02:07:49,400
The Holy Father didn't see it like that.

1434
02:07:49,400 --> 02:07:51,400
He urged him to go public.

1435
02:07:51,500 --> 02:07:53,500
His Holiness thought that the discovery

1436
02:07:53,500 --> 02:07:57,500
could actually scientifically prove the existence of a divine power.

1437
02:07:57,800 --> 02:08:00,900
And begin to bridge the gap between science and religion.

1438
02:08:00,900 --> 02:08:03,800
His work was not religious. It was sacrilegious.

1439
02:08:03,800 --> 02:08:09,000
But you...You saw the pope's position as a softening of church law.

1440
02:08:09,500 --> 02:08:13,400
As an old man's weakness. Your father's weakness.

1441
02:08:13,800 --> 02:08:15,600
You murdered the Vicar of Christ.

1442
02:08:15,600 --> 02:08:19,600
He raised me to protect this Church...even from within.

1443
02:08:19,700 --> 02:08:25,000
Then you conjured up an old enemy from the past. The Illuminati.

1444
02:08:25,800 --> 02:08:30,100
You found the ancient brands in the papal vaults and put them to use...

1445
02:08:30,100 --> 02:08:31,300
to spread fear!

1446
02:08:31,300 --> 02:08:33,900
The Cardinals are men of belief.

1447
02:08:33,900 --> 02:08:37,600
Right now, their belief in evil is uniting them.

1448
02:08:37,600 --> 02:08:40,900
The entire Catholic world will be united by this attack.

1449
02:08:40,900 --> 02:08:43,100
There is no attack.

1450
02:08:43,800 --> 02:08:46,800
You're trying to convince the Cardinals they're in a war...

1451
02:08:46,800 --> 02:08:49,000
so they will choose a warrior to lead them.

1452
02:08:49,100 --> 02:08:50,300
We are at war.

1453
02:08:50,400 --> 02:08:52,500
We're weak when we should be strong.

1454
02:08:52,500 --> 02:08:56,500
If science is allowed to claim the power of creation...

1455
02:08:56,500 --> 02:08:58,300
what is left for God?

1456
02:08:58,400 --> 02:09:00,300
It didn't work, Patrick.

1457
02:09:01,500 --> 02:09:05,200
-It isn't finished. - Oh, yes, it's finished.

1458
02:09:06,100 --> 02:09:08,300
It's finished.

1459
02:09:09,000 --> 02:09:12,000
I've shown the journals to Father Simeon.

1460
02:09:12,000 --> 02:09:14,500
The moment the doors to the Conclave open...

1461
02:09:14,500 --> 02:09:17,700
he will tell the Cardinals what you've done.

1462
02:09:18,000 --> 02:09:20,800
I was planning on doing this alone.

1463
02:09:23,400 --> 02:09:25,100
Put it down.

1464
02:09:27,500 --> 02:09:30,400
But, perhaps, it's better that you're here.

1465
02:09:30,400 --> 02:09:31,800
Put it down.

1466
02:09:33,400 --> 02:09:35,400
Put it away.

1467
02:09:47,500 --> 02:09:50,800
Help. He's the one. He's got a gun.

1468
02:09:54,300 --> 02:09:56,700
- Illuminatus. - You bastard.

1469
02:09:56,800 --> 02:09:59,600
- Illuminatus! - You bastard!

1470
02:10:03,600 --> 02:10:05,700
Padre.

1471
02:10:14,700 --> 02:10:18,000
And get the helicopter for the older cardinals, right?

1472
02:10:21,500 --> 02:10:22,600
Robert?

1473
02:10:22,800 --> 02:10:25,600
The brand, the symbol, could it have another meaning?

1474
02:11:08,900 --> 02:11:12,200
I've been summoned by the College of Cardinals.

1475
02:12:25,400 --> 02:12:26,800
Gently.

1476
02:12:26,800 --> 02:12:31,400
But within our walls.

1477
02:12:40,900 --> 02:12:43,100
He's on your side.

1478
02:13:32,100 --> 02:13:36,100
Father, into their hands I commend my spirit.

1479
02:14:29,500 --> 02:14:31,300
Church sources now confirm that

1480
02:14:31,300 --> 02:14:33,700
Carmelengo,Father Patrick McKenna

1481
02:14:33,800 --> 02:14:38,700
has died of internal injuries sustained in his heroic fall...

1482
02:14:38,700 --> 02:14:41,000
The Catholic church thanks Camerlengo

1483
02:14:41,000 --> 02:14:45,000
for his selfless act and demands his immediate canonization.

1484
02:14:45,200 --> 02:14:49,000
The Vatican has also confirmed the deaths of three Cardinals

1485
02:14:49,000 --> 02:14:51,700
and the fire in the Santa Maria della Vittoria.

1486
02:14:51,700 --> 02:14:54,300
As we await the appearance of the new Holy Father

1487
02:14:54,400 --> 02:14:56,100
Cardinal Baggia of Italy...

1488
02:14:56,100 --> 02:14:59,900
one of the four original Preferiti...

1489
02:14:59,900 --> 02:15:02,200
who, despite terrorist attempts at disruption...

1490
02:15:02,200 --> 02:15:04,800
seems to have been selected in one of the swiftest and smoothest conclaves

1491
02:15:04,800 --> 02:15:06,900
in modern church history.

1492
02:15:13,600 --> 02:15:15,800
Professor Langdon? Please.

1493
02:15:32,900 --> 02:15:36,400
A token of thanks from His Holiness...

1494
02:15:36,400 --> 02:15:39,800
and from his new Camerlengo.

1495
02:15:40,800 --> 02:15:43,700
We are grateful you saved his life.

1496
02:15:43,700 --> 02:15:47,100
And it's our understanding that you require this text...

1497
02:15:47,200 --> 02:15:49,500
to complete your scholary work.

1498
02:15:51,200 --> 02:15:54,500
We ask only that in your last grand testament...

1499
02:15:54,500 --> 02:15:57,000
you ensure

1500
02:15:57,000 --> 02:15:59,200
it finds its way home.

1501
02:16:01,700 --> 02:16:02,900
Of course.

1502
02:16:02,900 --> 02:16:05,300
And when you write of us...

1503
02:16:05,300 --> 02:16:08,300
and you will write of us...

1504
02:16:08,300 --> 02:16:10,700
may I ask one thing?

1505
02:16:10,700 --> 02:16:12,600
Do so gently.

1506
02:16:14,800 --> 02:16:16,500
I'll try.

1507
02:16:16,500 --> 02:16:18,600
Religion is flawed...

1508
02:16:19,000 --> 02:16:22,000
but only because man is flawed.

1509
02:16:22,000 --> 02:16:25,700
All men, including this one.

1510
02:16:40,000 --> 02:16:42,100
He chose the name Luke.

1511
02:16:44,800 --> 02:16:47,800
There's been many Marks and Johns.

1512
02:16:49,200 --> 02:16:51,100
Never a Luke.

1513
02:16:51,500 --> 02:16:53,100
It said he was a doctor.

1514
02:16:54,200 --> 02:16:58,200
It's quite a message. Science and faith, all in one.

1515
02:16:58,400 --> 02:17:00,300
The world is in need of both.

1516
02:17:02,900 --> 02:17:05,600
You'll counsel him wisely.

1517
02:17:05,600 --> 02:17:09,500
I'm an old man. I'll counsel him briefly.

1518
02:17:14,800 --> 02:17:17,200
Mr. Langdon.

1519
02:17:22,000 --> 02:17:27,000
Thanks be to God for sending someone to protect this church.

1520
02:17:30,900 --> 02:17:33,700
I don't believe He sent me, Father.

1521
02:17:33,700 --> 02:17:36,200
Oh, my son.

1522
02:17:36,200 --> 02:17:38,500
Of course He did.

